author: Felicia Schwartz
title: U.S. Imposes Embargo on Arms to South Sudan
text:
WASHINGTON—The U.S. imposed an arms embargo on South Sudan Friday, in a sign of Washington’s mounting frustration with continued violence in the country.
The move is more symbolic than practical, as the U.S. government doesn’t sell arms or provide defense services to South Sudan, and there is virtually no military trade between the two countries.
